: 261}, {\"ngram\": \"a very promising Olympic trials\", \"from\": 280, \"to\": 311}, {\"ngram\": \"expectations\", \"from\": 329, \"to\": 341}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 377, \"to\": 381}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With these high expectations, Jamaicans at home and in the Diaspora are prepared to celebrate every victory, be it in the rounds or in the final of an event.\", \"from\": 384, \"to\": 541, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 414, \"end\": 423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1434390006839938e-20, \"text\": \"Jamaicans\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}, {\"begin\": 443, \"end\": 451, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_diaspora\", \"score\": 0.9999809465962985, \"rank\": 1.8939943644894385e-05, \"text\": \"Diaspora\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_diaspora\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_diaspora\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these high expectations\", \"from\": 389, \"to\": 412}, {\"ngram\": \"home\", \"from\": 427, \"to\": 431}, {\"ngram\": \"every victory\", \"from\": 478, \"to\": 491}, {\"ngram\": \"the rounds\", \"from\": 502, \"to\": 512}, {\"ngram\": \"the final\", \"from\": 519, \"to\": 528}, {\"ngram\": \"an event\", \"from\": 532, \"to\": 540}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A mode of celebration that has become commonplace over the last few Olympics or World Championships (or other victory celebrations) is the knocking of pot covers, referred to by many as 'knockivity'.\", \"from\": 542, \"to\": 741, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A mode\", \"from\": 542, \"to\": 548}, {\"ngram\": \"celebration\", \"from\": 552, \"to\": 563}, {\"ngram\": \"the last few Olympics\", \"from\": 597, \"to\": 618}, {\"ngram\": \"World Championships\", \"from\": 622, \"to\": 641}, {\"ngram\": \"other victory celebrations\", \"from\": 646, \"to\": 672}, {\"ngram\": \"the knocking\", \"from\": 677, \"to\": 689}, {\"ngram\": \"pot covers\", \"from\": 693, \"to\": 703}, {\"ngram\": \"knockivity\", \"from\": 729, \"to\": 739}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The individual that has become most synonymous with this aspect of the Jamaican culture is Dalton Spence, who has attained celebrity-like status at the National Stadium with his Dutch pot covers.\", \"from\": 743, \"to\": 938, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 814, \"end\": 822, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9993638521467159, \"rank\": 0.0006365527950653669, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 834, \"end\": 840, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Dalton\", \"score\": 0.9998612155012796, \"rank\": 0.00013880376251241254, \"text\": \"Dalton\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Dalton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Dalton\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The individual\", \"from\": 743, \"to\": 757}, {\"ngram\": \"this aspect\", \"from\": 795, \"to\": 806}, {\"ngram\": \"celebrity-like status\", \"from\": 866, \"to\": 887}, {\"ngram\": \"the National Stadium\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 911}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Spence is a music teacher at Christel House Jamaica in Spanish Town and describes his \\\"potcova\\\" ritual as a way of supporting and celebrating the greatness of all aspects of Jamaica, particularly on the world stage.\", \"from\": 939, \"to\": 1154, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 977, \"end\": 982, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/House_music\", \"score\": 0.9999999996052793, \"rank\": 3.884335742080815e-10, \"text\": \"House\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/House_music\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/House_music\"}, {\"begin\": 983, \"end\":